    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Ralph W. Seager (1911-2008) was born in Geneva, New York an November 3, 1911. He graduated from Penn Yan Academy in 1928 and studied verse through a University of California extension course from 1950-1951. He also studied verse at the University of New Hampshire Writer's Conference in 1954. Since 1938,
he has served as a postal clerk in Penn Yan and since 1960 he has been teaching creative verse writing at Keuka College. During World War II, he served in the South Pacific with the United States Navy.</p><p>Mr. Seager is the author of four books of verse; <emph render="italic">Songs from a Willow Whistle</emph>, <emph render="italic">Beyond the Green Gate</emph>,<emph render="italic"> Christmas Chimes in Rhyme</emph>, and <emph render="italic">Cup, Flagon and Fountain</emph>. His poems appear frequently in national magazines and he is also the author of <emph render="italic">Sound of an Echo</emph>, a book of prose.</p><p>Mr. and Mrs. Seager had three sons.  Mr. Seager resides in Penn Yan, NY.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The <emph render="bold">Ralph W. Seager Papers</emph> include biographical material, correspondence, manuscripts, galley proofs, photographs and published material.  This collection also contains a number of unprocessed additions.</p><p><emph render="bold">Correspondence</emph> includes   incoming and outgoing correspondence. (See also: Subject Files).</p><p><emph render="bold">Subject Files</emph> includes  correspondence, manuscripts, galley proofs, photographs and published material arranged alphabetically by subject. It includes manuscripts of all of Mr. Seager's books as well as published copies of each book, correspondence, galley proofs and other material relating to their publication.
Material covers the periods of 1954-1959 and 1961-1966.</p><p><emph render="bold">Manuscripts</emph>  consists of a manuscript of an article by Mr. Seager, a draft of an untitled poem, and a copy of a lecture.  (See also: Subject Files).</p><p><emph render="bold">Published Material</emph> consists of newspaper clippings, magazine articles by Mr. Seager, and a reprint of one of his poems.  (See also: Subject Files).
 Inclusive Dates: 1954-1966, undated.</p><p>Additional material was added to the end of the collection on Feb 12 1968, and can be found in Box 6.  Other material has been added since that has not yet been processed.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
      <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
      <p>The <emph render="bold">Ralph W. Seager Papers</emph> consist of four parts: <emph render="bold">Correspondence</emph>, <emph render="bold">Subject Files</emph>, <emph render="bold">Manuscripts</emph>, and <emph render="bold">Published Material</emph>.  All items are arranged in alphabetical order according to subject matter or type of material (book, periodical, etc.)</p>
    </arrangement>
